00:00:00.467 --> 00:00:04.567
♪♪

00:00:04.567 --> 00:00:06.067
Narrator:
THE DeLOREAN SPORTS CAR

00:00:06.067 --> 00:00:08.334
WAS MANUFACTURED
IN NORTHERN IRELAND

00:00:08.334 --> 00:00:10.234
IN THE EARLY 1980s.

00:00:10.234 --> 00:00:13.801
WITH GULL-WING DOORS AND BRUSHED
STAINLESS-STEEL PANELS,

00:00:13.801 --> 00:00:16.767
THE DeLOREAN WAS KNOWN
FOR ITS FLASHY STYLE.

00:00:16.767 --> 00:00:19.767
TODAY, MANY OF THESE CARS
ARE IN ROUGH SHAPE,

00:00:19.767 --> 00:00:23.868
BUT A RESTORATION CAN MAKE
A DeLOREAN LOOK LIKE NEW.

00:00:23.868 --> 00:00:26.067
[ MELLOW FUNK PLAYS ]

00:00:26.067 --> 00:00:31.334
THIS DeLOREAN IS A RARE
RELIC FROM THE '80s.

00:00:31.334 --> 00:00:36.501
ONLY 9,080 OF THESE ICONIC
CARS WERE MANUFACTURED.

00:00:36.501 --> 00:00:38.367
NO LONGER OPERATIONAL,

00:00:38.367 --> 00:00:41.300
THIS DeLOREAN MIGHT HAVE BEEN
DESTINED FOR THE JUNKYARD,

00:00:41.300 --> 00:00:43.467
BUT WITH PROFESSIONAL
RESTORATION,

00:00:43.467 --> 00:00:46.601
THIS COMPANY HAS THE SPARE PARTS
TO GET IT UP AND RUNNING.

00:00:46.601 --> 00:00:48.434
♪♪

00:00:48.434 --> 00:00:51.834
THE PROCESS STARTS
WITH THE DIAGNOSTICS.

00:00:51.834 --> 00:00:54.434
THE TECHNICIAN EXAMINES
THE SUSPENSION,

00:00:54.434 --> 00:00:56.667
THE STEERING RACK, AND BRAKES.

00:00:56.667 --> 00:00:59.467
HE FINDS SIGNIFICANT
DETERIORATION

00:00:59.467 --> 00:01:02.167
AND DOCUMENTS HIS FINDINGS.

00:01:02.167 --> 00:01:05.267
HE SCRUTINIZES EVERY PART
OF THE OLD DeLOREAN

00:01:05.267 --> 00:01:08.834
AND PRODUCES AN 11-PAGE
REPORT ON ITS CONDITION.

00:01:08.834 --> 00:01:10.434
♪♪

00:01:10.434 --> 00:01:13.200
ONCE ALL THE PROBLEMS
HAVE BEEN IDENTIFIED,

00:01:13.200 --> 00:01:15.367
THE MECHANIC GETS TO WORK,

00:01:15.367 --> 00:01:18.267
REMOVING PLUGS TO DRAIN
SOME OF THE COOLANT.

00:01:18.267 --> 00:01:20.868
HE DISASSEMBLES
MANY PIPES AND HOSES

00:01:20.868 --> 00:01:24.000
THAT RUN COOLANT FROM THE
RADIATOR TO THE REAR ENGINE.

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:27.167
♪♪

00:01:27.167 --> 00:01:29.868
MANY OF THE COOLANT PIPES
WILL NEED TO BE CLEANED

00:01:29.868 --> 00:01:31.801
IN ORDER TO BE REUSED.

00:01:31.801 --> 00:01:33.968
THE RUBBER HOSES
CAN'T BE SALVAGED

00:01:33.968 --> 00:01:36.234
AND WILL NEED REPLACEMENT.

00:01:36.234 --> 00:01:38.901
THE MECHANIC DISASSEMBLES
THE BRAKES.

00:01:38.901 --> 00:01:43.534
THE CALIPERS ARE IN BAD SHAPE,
BUT CAN BE REBUILT.

00:01:43.534 --> 00:01:45.968
THE RUSTY ROTORS
ARE STILL THICK ENOUGH

00:01:45.968 --> 00:01:47.601
THAT THEY CAN BE RESURFACED.

00:01:47.601 --> 00:01:50.234
♪♪

00:01:50.234 --> 00:01:51.767
AFTER MOUNTING NEW TIRES

00:01:51.767 --> 00:01:54.801
AND REFINISHING
THE CAST ALLOY WHEELS,

00:01:54.801 --> 00:01:58.601
ANOTHER TECHNICIAN
BOLTS THEM TO THE HUBS.

00:01:58.601 --> 00:02:02.934
HE LOWERS THE HOIST
AND SETS THE CAR ON THE FLOOR.

00:02:02.934 --> 00:02:05.968
HE TIGHTENS THE LUG NUTS
TO THE FINAL TORQUE SETTING.

00:02:05.968 --> 00:02:08.200
♪♪

00:02:08.200 --> 00:02:10.267
A TECHNICIAN
BEGINS DISASSEMBLING

00:02:10.267 --> 00:02:12.234
THE REAR-DRIVE ENGINE.

00:02:12.234 --> 00:02:14.834
IN ORDER TO KNOW
WHAT NEEDS TO BE REPLACED,

00:02:14.834 --> 00:02:17.868
THE TECHNICIAN MUST
TAKE THE ENGINE APART.

00:02:17.868 --> 00:02:20.067
HE REMOVES THE AIR FILTER BOX

00:02:20.067 --> 00:02:23.200
IN ORDER TO ACCESS
THE INTAKE MANIFOLD.

00:02:23.200 --> 00:02:26.501
THEN, HE UNBOLTS
THE W-SHAPED MANIFOLD PIPE

00:02:26.501 --> 00:02:30.167
THAT SPLITS THE AIR FLOW
TO THE ENGINE.

00:02:30.167 --> 00:02:34.067
ONCE IT'S OFF, HE REMOVES
THE AIR-MIXTURE CONTROL UNIT,

00:02:34.067 --> 00:02:36.901
WHICH NEEDS
RESTORATIVE WORK.

00:02:36.901 --> 00:02:38.968
WITH THE UNIT OUT OF THE WAY,

00:02:38.968 --> 00:02:43.100
HE CAN EASILY GET TO OTHER PARTS
THAT NEED REPLACING OR FIXING.

00:02:43.100 --> 00:02:47.267
THOSE INCLUDE SPARK PLUGS,
WIRES, VACUUM LINES,

00:02:47.267 --> 00:02:50.334
THE DISTRIBUTOR CAP,
AND ROTOR.

00:02:50.334 --> 00:02:53.567
UNDER THE FRONT HOOD,
THE MECHANIC PULLS THE FUEL PUMP

00:02:53.567 --> 00:02:57.067
OUT OF THE GAS TANK
TO CHECK FOR DETERIORATION.

00:02:57.067 --> 00:02:58.868
IT'S BEYOND REPAIR.

00:02:58.868 --> 00:03:02.901
HE DRAINS ANY FUEL
THAT REMAINS IN THE TANK.

00:03:02.901 --> 00:03:05.934
AFTER THE GAS TANK HAS BEEN
EMPTIED AND CLEANED,

00:03:05.934 --> 00:03:09.334
HE INSERTS A NEW,
MODERN-STYLE PUMP MODULE.

00:03:09.334 --> 00:03:12.567
ANOTHER TECHNICIAN HOLDS
THE TOP OF THE PUMP DOWN

00:03:12.567 --> 00:03:14.701
AS THE MODULE IS CLAMPED
INTO PLACE.

00:03:14.701 --> 00:03:17.767
♪♪

00:03:17.767 --> 00:03:21.367
NEXT, THE TECHNICIAN REMOVES
THE INTERIOR DOOR PANELS

00:03:21.367 --> 00:03:24.968
AND USES A CENTRAL TESTER
TO OPERATE THE POWER WINDOWS.

00:03:24.968 --> 00:03:27.367
♪♪

00:03:27.367 --> 00:03:30.200
HE CONFIRMS THE POWER WINDOWS
ARE FUNCTIONAL.

00:03:30.200 --> 00:03:33.200
HE ALSO CHECKS
THE POWER LOCKS AND MIRRORS

00:03:33.200 --> 00:03:35.400
TO VERIFY THAT
THEY'RE WORKING PROPERLY.

00:03:35.400 --> 00:03:37.234
♪♪

00:03:37.234 --> 00:03:40.167
HE PULLS OFF
EXTERIOR RUBBER TRIM.

00:03:40.167 --> 00:03:43.367
HE SHAVES OFF ANY REMAINING
RUBBER BITS.

00:03:43.367 --> 00:03:45.901
THIS ALLOWS ROOM
TO REPAIR A DENT

00:03:45.901 --> 00:03:48.968
IN THE STAINLESS-STEEL BODY.

00:03:48.968 --> 00:03:53.100
HE FILES THE AREA AROUND THE
DENT TO REMOVE SOME SCRATCHES.

00:03:53.100 --> 00:03:55.033
♪♪

00:03:55.033 --> 00:03:58.100
HE PLACES A SPECIAL TOOL
OVER THE DENT.

00:03:58.100 --> 00:04:01.868
IT HAS A ROD WITH A FINE STEEL
TIP THAT WELDS TO THE BODY,

00:04:01.868 --> 00:04:05.701
PROVIDING A SOLID GRIP AS HE
MANUALLY PULLS OUT THE DENT.

00:04:05.701 --> 00:04:07.334
♪♪

00:04:07.334 --> 00:04:10.067
MEANWHILE, ANOTHER
MECHANIC APPLIES TAPE

00:04:10.067 --> 00:04:13.801
TO VARIOUS SECTIONS OF THE CAR,
TO ESTABLISH BORDERS

00:04:13.801 --> 00:04:17.300
FOR THE REFINISHING
OF THE STEEL BODY PANELS.

00:04:17.300 --> 00:04:21.968
HE SANDS OUT ANY IMPERFECTIONS
OR TOOL MARKS FROM THE REPAIRS

00:04:21.968 --> 00:04:25.934
AND RESTORES THE BRUSHED
FINISH BUMPER TO BUMPER.

00:04:25.934 --> 00:04:28.100
SINCE NO PAINT CAN BE USED

00:04:28.100 --> 00:04:31.100
TO COVER UP REPAIRS
ON BARE STAINLESS STEEL,

00:04:31.100 --> 00:04:35.067
THE BODYWORK MUST BE
DONE PERFECTLY.

00:04:35.067 --> 00:04:38.334
INSIDE, TECHNICIANS
REUPHOLSTER THE SEATS

00:04:38.334 --> 00:04:40.033
AND TREAT ANY DISCOLORATION

00:04:40.033 --> 00:04:42.534
IN THE VINYL PANELS
AND DASHBOARD.

00:04:42.534 --> 00:04:47.634
FINALLY, THE ENTIRE CAR GETS
AN EXTENSIVE EXTERIOR CLEANING.

00:04:47.634 --> 00:04:51.100
IT'S TAKEN MONTHS TO RESTORE
THIS DeLOREAN,

00:04:51.100 --> 00:04:52.701
BUT THE QUESTION REMAINS:

00:04:52.701 --> 00:04:55.234
WILL IT RUN LIKE A NEW CAR?

00:04:55.234 --> 00:04:58.100
ONCE TESTED IN VARIOUS
DRIVING CONDITIONS,

00:04:58.100 --> 00:05:01.601
MECHANICS CONFIRM
THAT THIS 1980s THROWBACK

00:05:01.601 --> 00:05:03.934
IS READY FOR ITS COMEBACK.

